data.description: Presenting an exceptional split-level residence in Turning Stone subdivision, where luxury meets space on one of the largest lot in the neighborhood. Situated on an expansive .39-acre parcel at the end of a tranquil cul-de-sac, this home offers an unparalleled sense of privacy, with one side thoughtfully separated from neighbors by a subdivision easement. Step into a generously designed open floor plan, where the large living room seamlessly transitions into the dining area and island kitchen. This culinary haven features a breakfast bar, recessed lighting, stainless steel appliances, and abundant cabinetry for all your storage needs. The primary suite, along with all bedrooms, is strategically located on the lower level, offering a private retreat. The primary suite boasts an en-suite bath with a soaking tub and walk-in shower. Venture upstairs to discover a substantial family/game room, versatile enough to function as a fifth bedroom, media room, or home office. Outside, the backyard beckons with an extended patio, privacy fence, and an expansive lawn-a perfect outdoor oasis. Beyond aesthetics, practicality abounds with the addition of a 400 Amp breaker box, ensuring seamless electrical functionality. The strategic location places you in proximity to schools, parks, community amenities, shopping, and provides easy access to I-35 and 1604. As an added benefit, the seller is offering closing cost assistance to buyers, making this opportunity even more enticing.  This residence epitomizes comfort, style, and convenience-seize the chance to make it yours by booking your personal tour today.
